SPERMATHECAE. Moderately narrow and relatively short, with large globular lateral receptacles (
Fig. 208
).

Carapace length in males varies from 4.42 to 5.57, in females from 4.70 to 6.45. The dorsal abdominal pattern in specimens collected from eastern, less humid part of the geographical range, is weakly developed to indistinct. In some females, independent of the localities they were taken from, the posterior half of the carapace looks somewhat lighter in colour than the anterior one (as in specimens T.S. Mcheidze used to describe as 

Brachythele recki

). The structure of the spermathecae in all females examined shows a quite insignificant variation (see 
Figs 208–209
).
